title: SpaceX rolls out Falcon 9 rocket for Starlink launch
summary: Another 53 Starlink internet satellites are ready to rocket into orbit Friday from Cape Canaveral on a SpaceX Falcon 9 rocket. The two-stage Falcon 9, powered by a reusable booster, will place the 53 internet relay nodes into a low-altitude transfer orbit.

title: Kentucky, Oklahoma Students to Hear from NASA Astronaut in Space
summary: Students from Kentucky and Oklahoma will have the opportunity next week to hear from NASA astronaut Jessica Watkins aboard the International Space Station.

title: SpaceX to launch third Starlink mission in less than two weeks
summary: SpaceX is set to launch another batch of Starlink satellites into Low-Earth Orbit (LEO) onboard a Falcon 9 rocket as part of the Starlink Group 4-27 mission. Liftoff is scheduled for Friday, August 19 at 3:21:20 PM EDT (19:21:20 UTC) from Space Launch Complex 40 (SLC-40), at the Cape Canaveral Space Force Station in Florida.

title: Dragon cargo ship departs space station, heads for splashdown near Florida
summary: A SpaceX Dragon supply freighter undocked from the International Space Station Friday, heading for splashdown off the coast of Florida Saturday with about two tons of cargo, experiments, and a leaky spacesuit.

title: NASA Sets Launch Coverage for Artemis Mega Moon Rocket, Spacecraft
summary: NASA will provide coverage of prelaunch, launch, and postlaunch activities for Artemis I, the first integrated test of NASA’s Orion spacecraft, Space Launch System (SLS) rocket, and the ground systems at the agency’s Kennedy Space Center in Florida.

title: NASA selects astrophysics mission proposals for study
summary: NASA has selected four mission concepts for additional study in the latest round of an astrophysics program, but selected missions could face delays because of budget constraints.

title: Maxar receives delayed Ovzon 3 satellite parts
summary: Ovzon’s first satellite is set to launch between December and February following the delivery of parts caught up in supply chain delays, the Swedish broadband service provider said Aug. 18.

title: SpaceX’s next-gen Starship rocket wins first satellite launch contract

title: NASA Selects Proposals to Study Stellar Explosions, Galaxies, Stars
summary: NASA has selected four mission proposals submitted to the agency’s Explorers Program for further study.
